				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The unpopulated circuitry is meant to make a NTSC PPU work on PAL-M TVs by replacing just the color crystal with the 21.45666 one.<br /><br />That's what Playtronic NES units do. Legit Ricoh NTSC PPU and a &quot;correction&quot; circuit which changes the video to PAL.  Unfortunately the colors will be a little off with that transcodification method...<br /><br />Since your unit doesn't have the circuit you want to fit it with either a UM6548 PPU or keep your UM6528 PPU and install a NTSC clock crystal.<br /><br />I honestly prefer NTSC NES than PAL-M NES but that's me.  All of my TVs can accept NTSC signals.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
